text: Lénaïg Corson (born on 15 March 1989) is a French rugby sevens and rugby union player. She particpated at the 2014 Women's Rugby World Cup, 2017 Women's Rugby World Cup, and 2019 Women’s Rugby Super Series. == References == Category:1989 births Category:Living people Category:French rugby union players Category:Rugby sevens players Category:People from Côtes-d'Armor Category:Sportspeople from Brittany
